A ∩ B = {2, 3}

Now, let's find the symmetric difference of A and B, which is denoted by A ∆ B. This set contains all the elements that are in either A or B, but not in both.

A ∆ B = {1, 4}

Finally, let's find the symmetric difference of (A ∩ B) and (A ∆ B). This set contains all the elements that are in either (A ∩ B) or (A ∆ B), but not in both.

(A ∩ B) ∆ (A ∆ B) = {1, 2, 3, 4}

So, the symmetric difference of (A ∩ B) and (A ∆ B) is {1, 2, 3, 4}.
